{
  "texts": [
    "The TestChain framework [84] enables LLMs to interact with a Python interpreter, leveraging actual execution results to construct correct expected outputs, thereby effectively resolving assertion failures caused by calculation errors.",
    "Execution-aware test completion re-ranking (TECO) similarly reduces logical oracle errors [100].",
    "Furthermore, specific types of assertions, such as those verifying exception throwing, remain a significant challenge for current LLMs, with studies showing that even advanced frameworks completely fail to generate any correct exception assertions [78].Poor Maintainability.",
    "This challenge pertains to the long-term value and engineering quality of generated test suites, as unmaintainable tests can become technical debt whose cost outweighs their initial benefits.",
    "Beyond functional correctness, the maintainability of generated tests is another critical issue."
  ]
}